summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about barley yields

properties.description: The yield of barley in bushels per acre
The year in which the barley was harvested
The location where the barley was grown

goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving a good idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary by variety?
goals.visualization: grouped bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A grouped bar chart can show the yield for each variety side-by-side, making it easy to compare the yields and identify any patterns or differences.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield at each site?
goals.rationale: A histogram can show the frequency distribution of yield at each site, giving an idea of the shape of the distribution and any differences between sites.

goals.question: How does the yield change over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of yield by year
goals.rationale: A line chart can show the trend in yield over time, making it easy to see if there are any patterns or changes in yield from year to year.

goals.question: Is there a relationship between yield and location?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by location
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and location, making it easy to see if there are any patterns or correlations between the two variables.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='yield', data=data)
    plt.axvline(x=data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Yield: {:.2f}'.format(data['yield'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.catplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data, kind='bar', ci=None, palette='muted', alpha=0.7)
    chart.set_xticklabels(rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('How does the yield vary by variety?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', hue='site', multiple='stack', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Yield: {:.2f}'.format(data['yield'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield at each site?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
